-- Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro, Repsol and YPF Were Active
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-04-18T21:09:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-repsol-and-ypf-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the close in Buenos
Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  index fell 0.9 percent to 2,357.67.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)   rose 3.4 percent to 8.74 pesos, its
biggest gain in three months. Local investors are buying local
stocks after a recent slump as they are trading at “discount”
prices, Juan Jose Vasquez, an analyst at Bull Market Brokers SA,
said in an interview from Buenos Aires.  YPF SA (YPFD)  , Argentina’s largest oil company, slumped
a record 29 percent to 77.05 pesos. The government rejected
 Repsol YPF SA (REP) ’s demand for $10.5 billion in compensation for the
unit’s nationalization. The shares of Repsol YPF SA (REP AF)
that trade in Buenos Aires lost 4.6 percent to 113 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
